  "scenario_brief": "PATROL OVERRIDE TEST (Phase 2-4)\n\nThis scenario tests the patrolOverride and speed/dwell actions (npc-behavior.js goToAndStay method).\n\nTEST PROCEDURE:\n1. Game starts — observe nurse patrolling between Station (5,3) → Bed1 (2,5) → Bed2 (8,5)\n2. Normal patrol cycle takes ~15 seconds per leg\n3. Interact with the EMERGENCY BUTTON in the room\n4. This triggers 'emergency_activated' global = true\n5. OBSERVE: Nurse immediately abandons patrol\n6. Nurse walks directly to Emergency Station (5,8) at faster speed (150px/s vs 80px/s)\n7. Nurse stands at Emergency Station with no dwell time\n8. Monitor NPC says: 'Emergency response engaged'\n\nEXPECTED BEHAVIOR:\n- Nurse never completes current patrol leg (immediate interrupt)\n- Direct path to emergency location (not following patrol waypoints)\n- Visibly faster movement speed\n- Stops at destination and remains stationary\n\nTEST DURATION: 1-2 minutes\n\nKEY VALIDATION:\n✓ goToAndStay() successfully interrupts patrol\n✓ Speed increase is visibly noticeable\n✓ NPC reaches target and stops permanently\n✓ patrolOverride action triggers correctly",
  "endGoal": "Verify nurse abandons patrol and walks to emergency location at increased speed.",
